  "event_preview": "Taupō International Motorsport Park is a 3.32 km (2.064-mile) permanent road circuit in Taupō, New Zealand, featuring 14 turns on a flowing anti-clockwise layout with elevation changes, high-speed straights and technical corners that reward precision and tyre management. The 2026 ITM Taupō Super 440 is Round 3 of the Repco Supercars Championship and the third visit for the series to the venue. The weekend consists of multiple races contested on the full International Circuit configuration. Racing here is an exercise in track position, clean lines and race craft — overtaking opportunities exist, but qualifying performance often proves decisive on the demanding New Zealand layout. The all-time Supercars qualifying lap record at Taupō belongs to Ryan Wood, who turned a 1:25.9778 lap in 2025. The fastest lap in race conditions — 1:27.5377, set by Broc Feeney during the 2025 Taupō Super 440 — remains the benchmark for race pace at the circuit.",
